07:56.260 --> 08:02.500
In Dragon's Egg, Ford takes a hard science approach to a situation in which beings who inhabit a neutron star

08:02.500 --> 08:06.940
learn of the humans who are orbiting their star, then establish communications with them.

08:07.420 --> 08:13.480
The task is made difficult, though, by the fact that the aliens live at a pace roughly a million times faster than that of humans.

08:13.940 --> 08:18.480
Thus an individual alien, or chila, lives out its entire life in several human minutes.

08:18.480 --> 08:24.240
The chila, being native to a neutron star, with its intense gravitational and magnetic fields

08:24.240 --> 08:28.260
and extremely dense matter, are certainly constructed different from humans.

08:28.840 --> 08:32.920
Here Ford tells us about the aliens, their environment, and their names.

08:33.660 --> 08:40.540
Once I had placed my imagination and myself on the surface of the neutron star,

08:40.540 --> 08:52.540
now once I knew the territory well enough, and appreciated the fact that the light on this star comes from below, not above.

08:53.240 --> 08:59.460
The sky is black, there's no light coming out of it except a few stars. Everything is a glow from below.

09:01.580 --> 09:06.140
The territory is very flat because of the terrific gravity.

09:07.200 --> 09:10.740
I began to sort of appreciate what it was like there.

09:13.320 --> 09:27.560
What I basically did was take the Indian technique of naming children about things that occurred shortly after they were born,

09:28.500 --> 09:34.600
and applied it to the chila, but put in a hyphen so it would take out the Indian context.

09:34.600 --> 09:44.880
And also, of course, a lot of the Indian things like eagles and feathers and the sky and things like that don't exist,

09:45.040 --> 09:46.760
so I had to do that transfer.

09:47.680 --> 09:51.800
The chila's social structure differs from ours as well, though there are some similarities.

09:52.480 --> 10:00.580
Soon I began to realize that in my dreaming up of these creatures, I'd end up with a social structure

10:00.580 --> 10:07.280
that was sort of halfway between a Scottish clan and an Indian tribe,

10:08.400 --> 10:20.440
and as if both the Indians and the Scottish were crocodiles that laid eggs instead of having the problems of mammals that they had to take care of their young.

10:21.300 --> 10:27.060
The younger, immediately viable, crocodiles and turtles, and so are the little tiny chila.

10:27.060 --> 10:42.680
So what I tried to do was imagine what it would be like if instead of monkeys developing intelligent social interactions, crocodiles developed intelligent social interactions.

